top1_content: There are numerous Work-Integrated Learning options, some of which are mandatory and others that are optional. As a Software Engineering student or enrolled in any of the professional degrees, you're required to take part in a year of industry placement and a 24-credit-point final year project. It's a requirement for all students to undertake a capstone project in their final year, involving a collaboration with an industry partner or an in-house project mimicking real industry situations. A project supervisor will be assigned to work with you closely. We also have summer projects and other industry events such as the ANZ hackathon, AIIA iAwards competition, and various coding or security competitions.
